From: DevBox UML arm64 Port
Subject: [PATCH 7/9] um/os-Linux/skas/process.c: arm64 compat + PTRACE_SYSCALL fallback

Three related changes needed for arm64 / Android non-root support:

1. PTRACE_GETREGS/SETREGS do not exist on arm64.
   Replace direct ptrace(PTRACE_GETREGS/SETREGS) calls with
   save_registers()/restore_registers() on arm64 via #ifdef __aarch64__.

2. PTRACE_SYSEMU is blocked by Android SELinux (and is not implemented
   in the arm64 kernel anyway).  Add a runtime fallback:

   When sysemu_supported == 0, use PTRACE_SYSCALL two-stop mode:
     - Entry stop  (SIGTRAP|0x80): save real syscall nr, replace with
       __NR_getpid so the host executes something harmless, continue.
     - Exit stop   (SIGTRAP|0x80): restore syscall nr, call handle_trap()
       to dispatch the syscall inside UML, write return value, continue.

   This is the same trick proot uses — Android SELinux allows
   PTRACE_SYSCALL (used by proot/debuggers) but not PTRACE_SYSEMU.

3. ptrace_dump_regs() uses PTRACE_GETREGS which doesn't exist on arm64.
   Guard with #ifndef __aarch64__ and provide an GETREGSET alternative.

diff --git a/arch/um/os-Linux/skas/process.c b/arch/um/os-Linux/skas/process.c
