+		/*
+		 * Choose ptrace run operation:
+		 *   sysemu_supported: use PTRACE_SYSEMU (one stop per syscall).
+		 *   !sysemu_supported (arm64/Android): use PTRACE_SYSCALL.
+		 *     - If we are at syscall entry, neutralise the syscall first
+		 *       so the host runs something harmless; we'll dispatch the
+		 *       real syscall at the exit stop.
+		 *     - If we are at syscall exit (at_syscall_entry just flipped
+		 *       to false by the handler below), the guest resumes normally.
